reviewText: This is not what I was looking for. Had seen a concert on tv of Vince Gill that was a couple of hours long. It had more people performing with him, and it was also filmed at the Ryman. This one is all acoustic, and even though I knew it was on VHS, I ordered because I thought it was the right one.

If you are a fan of Vince Gill as much as I am, then this is a collection of music that you must have.  He's very laid back and talks about each of the songs he's going to sing.  He is, in my opinion, the best country singer with a beautiful tenor voice that you never get tired of listening to.  Purchase it if you can.  It's very difficult to find.

The video quality is about what you'd expect for VHS, but the music comes through clear.  Vince Gill and a handful of top notch musicians doing acoustic versions of his hits in a small theater.  I liked it all way around, but I'm a fan.
I received this quickly, but the video and audio was beyond horrible...even for a vhs! I would love to return it!

This is an awesome concert by Vince Gill the only thing that could make it better is if they would please release it on DVD.  He included many of his gretaest hits, and it is performed in the Rhyman Auditorium. If you are a Vince Gill fan you will love this concert.
